  m_Name: InventoryTutorial
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  tutorialSteps:
  - title: Welcome to Xsolla Inventory SDK demo!
    description: Inventory SDK allows you to use Xsolla Player Inventory independently
      from our payment solution on platforms that for any reason prohibit the use
      of Xsolla In-Game Store and Pay Station.\n We will show you different ways to
      add items to your inventory in the tutorial.
    prevButtonText: NO, THANKS
    nextButtonText: "LET\u2019S START"
    highlightElementId: 
    screenToActivate: 0
    associatedDocumentation: 
  - title: 'In the demo, you can add items to the inventory in one of the following
      ways:'
    description: 1. Buy some items in the web shop\n2. Redeem a coupon code to get
      bonus items\n3. Link a platform account to your main account
    prevButtonText: BACK
    nextButtonText: NEXT
    highlightElementId: 
    screenToActivate: 0
    associatedDocumentation: 
  - title: Buy items in the web shop
    description: 1. Go to the web shop.\n2. Log in to the same account as you used
      for the demo.\n3. Buy some items. You can use our test cards.\n \n The items
      you purchased will be available in the inventory.
    prevButtonText: BACK
    nextButtonText: NEXT
    highlightElementId: WebStoreMenuButton
    screenToActivate: 2
    associatedDocumentation: 
  - title: Redeem a coupon code
    description: "1. Click the REDEEM COUPON button in the top navigation bar.\\n2.
      Enter one of our test codes \u201CBONUS2020\u201D or \u201CWINTER2021\u201D
      in the pop-up window.\\n \\n The items you purchased will be available in the
      inventory."
    prevButtonText: BACK
    nextButtonText: NEXT
    highlightElementId: RedeemCouponButton
    screenToActivate: 1
    associatedDocumentation: 
  - title: Account linking
    description: Use account linking to manage a single cross-platform inventory on
      different platforms. Check documentation to learn more about account linking
      in demo.\n \n1. Set up platform in the plug-in settings.\n2. Click Account Linking
      in the main menu. The demo project will open in the default browser to simulate
      the start of the application on another platform.\n3. Create an account or log
      in and purchase some items using one of the test bank cards.\n4. Click Get code
      and then click Request the code in the window that appears.\n5. Enter the received
      account linking code in the demo and click Confirm.\n \nItems from your main
      account will be available in the inventory after linking accounts is successful.
    prevButtonText: BACK
    nextButtonText: DONE
    highlightElementId: AccountLinkingMenuButton
    screenToActivate: 2
    associatedDocumentation: https://developers.xsolla.com/sdk/unity/use-xsolla-servers/how-tos/#unity_sdk_use_xsolla_servers_how_to_try_account_linking_in_demo
